ars) bridging loan for Condor to enable it to continue flying and save jobs. A precondition for the type of investor protection proceedings in Germany that is being used in the Condor case is that a company is not yet insolvent and can be saved. BBNaija Season 4: How Tacha, Mercy court summary eviction(Opens in a new browser tab) Condor and Thomas Cook GmbH, the second-biggest tour operator in Germany after TUI (TUIGn.DE), are both independent units of the insolvent British parent company. Lucas Floether, who is working on the wind up of Air Berlin, will supervise the process, Condor said. (NAN) Vanguard Thomas Cook staff were applauded after the travel company’s final flight landed in the UK today. The pilot of the Airbus A330 made an emotional address to passengers after touching down at Manchester Airport. Passengers told Sky News they comforted the crew, who faced possible redundancy, and held a “whip-round”… September 23, 2019 In "Foreign" Thomas Cook, the world’s oldest travel firm, collapsed on Monday, stranding hundreds of thousands of holidaymakers around the globe and sparking the largest peacetime repatriation effort in British history. September 23, 2019 In "News" The Italian Foreign Ministry set up a crisis management group and opened a hotline on Monday to help nationals stranded abroad after UK travel operator Thomas Cook filed for bankruptcy. September 23, 2019 In "News"